<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n22024i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n22" href="#n22024i">N22 (VI.B.17)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n22all.htm#n22024i"> 24(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Columban to Bonif IV / (JJ &amp; G. Rex) </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: Between 612 and 615, St. Columban wrote a letter to Pope Boniface at the request of king Agilulf on the subject of debated chapters which were considered by Rome to favour Nestorism. In August 1911 James Joyce wrote to King George V on the subject of disputed passages in <cite>Dubliners</cite>. </mm> </dd></dl>
